searchext is Vim plugin for search extension.

It acts as search command when 'incsearch' is set.
The difference is it searches for the occurrence of regexp generated by specified method.
For example it initiates migemo incremental search by typing "m/" under following mapping.

  noremap <expr> m/ searchext#IncSearch('m/', 'migemo')

==============================================================================
Functions:

searchext#IncSearch({prompt}, {method} [, {flags}])
		Initiate incremental search.

		The {prompt} argument is a prompt string.

		{method} is a String, which is a method name.  See Search method.

		{flags} is a String, which can contain these character flags:
		'b'	search backward instead of forward

searchext#FindChar({method} [, {flags}])
		Move to occurrence of a next input character like with the f command.

		{method} and {flags} is used like with searchext#IncSearch().

==============================================================================
Search method:

Search method is specified by name.
Search pattern is generated by function searchext#method#{method}#Regexp({pattern})
when search function such as searchext#IncSearch is invoked with method name {method}.
The argument {pattern} is input string.
The return value is search pattern.

For example the way to define search method 'literal' is to define following
function in "~/.vim/autoload/searchext/method/literal.vim".

  function searchext#method#literal#Regexp(pattern)
    return '\V' . escape(a:pattern, '\')
  endfunction


The list of search method:

migemo		Migemo search.
		This requires the +ruby feature.
		This requires migemo command setting like the following.

		  Example: let searchext#method#migemo#command = "nkf -Weu |migemo -t emacs /usr/share/migemo/migemo-dict -i '\t' |nkf -Ewu |sed -u 's/\\\\(/\\\\%(/g;s/\t//g'"
		  Example: let searchext#method#migemo#command = 'nkf -Weu |cmigemo -q -v -d /usr/share/migemo/migemo-dict |nkf -Ewu'

		Note: Unless command responds, Vim will freeze.

==============================================================================
Highlight:

searchextIncSearchAll	Incremental search highlighting; used for the all texts
			matching the search pattern but highlighted in IncSearch.

==============================================================================
Bugs:

The incremental search will break when some key (e.g. CTRL-R) is typed.

==============================================================================
Example setting:

  noremap <expr> <Leader>f searchext#FindChar('migemo')
  noremap <expr> <Leader>F searchext#FindChar('migemo', 'b')
  noremap <expr> m/ searchext#IncSearch('m/', 'migemo')
  noremap <expr> m? searchext#IncSearch('m?', 'migemo', 'b')
  let searchext#method#migemo#command = "nkf -Weu |migemo -t emacs /usr/share/migemo/migemo-dict -i '\t' |nkf -Ewu |sed -u 's/\\\\(/\\\\%(/g;s/\t//g'"
  hi searchextIncSearchAll ctermfg=Black ctermbg=Green guifg=Black guibg=Green
